                    "title": "<span style=\"font-size:26px;\">&nbsp;</span>",
                    "content": "<div class=\"footnotes\">\n<h5>Footnotes</h5>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li><a href=\"http://www.japaneselawtranslation.go.jp/law/detail/?id=3188&amp;vm=04&amp;re=01\" target=\"_blank\">Act on the Promotion of the Female Participation and Career Advancement in the Workplace, Act No. 64, 4 September 2015</a>. (\u21e1 back to text)</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.e-stat.go.jp/en/stat-search/files?page=1&amp;toukei=00200532&amp;tstat=000001107875\" target=\"_blank\">Government of Japan, Portal of Official Statistics of Japan, Employment Status Survey 2017</a>. (\u21e1 back to text)</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.stat.go.jp/english/data/roudou/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">Government of Japan, Statistics Bureau of Japan, Labour Force Survey 2019</a>. (\u21e1 back to text)</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.stat.go.jp/english/data/shugyou/4.html#05l3-4\" target=\"_blank\">Arubaito, refers to side-workers as a form of employment, Statistics Bureau of Japan, 1997, Employment Structure Survey: explanation of terms (last accessed on 17 September 2020)</a>. (\u21e1 back to text)</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n",
